29.43	The_godfather	The Godfather	The Godfather is a 1972 American epic crime film directed by Francis Ford Coppola and based on Mario Puzo's 1969 novel of the same name. The screenplay was written by Puzo, Coppola and an uncredited Robert Towne. The film stars Marlon Brando as Vito Corleone, the patriarch of the Italian-American Corleone family, and Al Pacino as Michael Corleone, Vito's son. It also stars James Caan, Richard S. Castellano, Robert Duvall, Sterling Hayden, John Marley, Richard Conte and Diane Keaton, and features John Cazale, Talia Shire, and Abe Vigoda. The story, spanning the years 1945 to 1955, centers on Michael's ascension from reluctant family outsider to ruthless Mafia boss while also chronicling the experiences of the Corleone family.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1c/Godfather_ver1.jpg/220px-Godfather_ver1.jpg
